    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-12-14T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-12-14T18:00:00-05:00" n="366"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d366">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/12–150: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in China</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-12-14T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 14, 1950—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>525. Urtel 723, Dec 1. Dept’s present view is that UN consideration status of
                    Formosa shld be postponed perhaps until next session <gloss target="#t_GA1"
                        >GA</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> has been instructed
                    accordingly (see Dept info agam Dec 8).<note n="1" xml:id="d366fn1">Not printed,
                        but see telegram <gloss target="#t_Gadel1">Gadel</gloss> 162, December 5, to
                        New York, <ref target="#pg_589">p. 589</ref>.</note> While foregoing is
                    present view this Govt you shld bear in mind that settlement nr outstanding
                    problems in Far East has become major concern of other members UN whose views
                    may influence to some degree at least timing and methods of settlement.</p>
                <p>You may in your discretion convey substance foregoing orally and confidentially
                    to <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss>s.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
